Date: 2000-01-26

Title: Vacuum Polarization in QED with World-Line Methods

Authors: W. Dittrich and R. Shaisultanov

Comments: 9 pages

Journal-ref: Phys.Rev. D62 (2000) 045024

Motivated by several recent papers on string-inspired calculations in QED, wehere present our own use of world-line techniques in order to calculate thevacuum polarization and effective action in scalar and spinor QED with externalarbitrary constant electromagnetic field configuration.